00:49.616 --> 00:51.140
(KISSING NOISES)

01:05.765 --> 01:07.323
Burt.

01:07.400 --> 01:08.662
What?
Don't.

01:08.735 --> 01:10.327
Why?

01:10.403 --> 01:11.927
Come back up here,
I want to kiss you.

01:12.005 --> 01:13.973
No, come on. I want to do this.
I'm staying down here.

01:14.040 --> 01:15.371
Okay.

01:17.243 --> 01:19.234
Just don't blow.
What?

01:20.046 --> 01:21.138
Don't blow.

01:21.214 --> 01:22.738
Why would I blow?

01:22.816 --> 01:24.807
I don't know why you do
anything you do, Burt.

01:24.884 --> 01:26.511
Just don't blow.

01:26.786 --> 01:29.721
Okay. Just stop
moving. Okay?
Okay.

01:29.789 --> 01:30.778
You'll love it.

01:30.857 --> 01:33.018
All right, no more talking.

01:33.093 --> 01:34.617
(KISSING NOISES)

01:36.663 --> 01:38.187
(BOTH MOANING)

01:46.840 --> 01:48.000
What's wrong?

01:48.074 --> 01:49.063
Nothing.

01:49.709 --> 01:51.267
Why'd you stop?

01:51.344 --> 01:55.178
I'm just trying to figure out how
to say what I'm about to say.

01:55.248 --> 01:57.944
Why do you have
to say anything?

01:58.017 --> 02:01.783
You taste different.
Did you know that?

02:02.622 --> 02:05.420
No, Burt.
How would I know that?

02:05.492 --> 02:08.393
Just get up here. Okay?
I don't want to keep talking
to the top of your head.

02:08.461 --> 02:09.655
Do you want me to shower?
No, no.

02:09.729 --> 02:12.254
You don't taste dirty.
You just taste different.

02:12.332 --> 02:14.630
Like, kind of fruity.

02:14.701 --> 02:15.895
God.

02:15.969 --> 02:19.530
Wait. Did you know a woman can taste
different depending on various co-factors?

02:19.606 --> 02:20.630
I don't want to hear that.

02:20.707 --> 02:23.175
And I thought that we agreed you
wouldn't use the word "co-factors."

02:23.243 --> 02:24.835
No, I said I wouldn't misuse it.

02:24.911 --> 02:28.039
All I'm saying is, from what
I've read about vaginal flavor...

02:28.114 --> 02:30.173
Jesus!
...from what I've read,

02:30.250 --> 02:34.118
abrupt changes can happen when
a woman's either menopausal

02:35.188 --> 02:36.382
or...

02:37.090 --> 02:38.455
(SNICKERS)

02:44.430 --> 02:46.091
(TAPPING)

02:55.842 --> 02:57.139
Burt?

02:58.311 --> 03:00.006
Oh! Good, you're awake.

03:00.079 --> 03:01.239
What are you doing?

03:02.949 --> 03:04.382
Cobbling.

03:04.450 --> 03:05.974
(VERONA LAUGHS)

03:07.720 --> 03:12.783
I really want to be that dad that knows
how to make stuff out of wood. You know?

03:13.459 --> 03:18.158
I just want our kid to wake up in the morning
and walk out on the back porch

03:18.231 --> 03:20.927
and find me cobbling.

03:21.634 --> 03:23.761
You know, that's not what it's called.

03:23.836 --> 03:25.201
Yeah, it is.

03:25.271 --> 03:27.432
Burt, cobbling is shoes.

03:28.174 --> 03:31.871
That's why the people that make shoes
are called cobblers.

03:32.345 --> 03:35.041
You're not cobbling,
you're carving.

03:35.114 --> 03:37.912
Or possibly whittling.

03:39.419 --> 03:41.387
Good morning.
Morning.

03:42.455 --> 03:44.548
BURT: I got this great book on knots.

03:44.624 --> 03:46.649
300 knots, and I'm gonna
learn them all.

03:46.726 --> 03:50.992
And I still have to build that kiln.
Man, you gotta be ready.

03:51.064 --> 03:53.089
You remember, we go to your
parents' house this afternoon?

03:53.166 --> 03:57.398
Yeah, you know, I pushed that because
I have Family Defense class today.

03:57.470 --> 03:59.529
Yeah. Does everybody
there dress like that?

03:59.606 --> 04:01.233
Hey, where are those
goggles you had?

04:01.307 --> 04:02.797
My airbrush ones?
Yeah.

04:02.875 --> 04:04.570
You can't use them.
Got them.

04:04.644 --> 04:05.633
Burt.

04:05.712 --> 04:07.373
All right.
I will be back at 3:00.

04:07.447 --> 04:10.678
Maybe a little later if I get into
some hand-to-hand combat.

04:10.750 --> 04:12.581
Okay, bye.
Bye.

04:24.197 --> 04:27.496
VERONA: They look like the
California Raisins, remember?

04:27.567 --> 04:31.003
The big bodies, the little legs
and the sunglasses.

04:31.070 --> 04:32.059
GRACE ON PHONE: Lovely.

04:32.138 --> 04:35.073
It's so bad. I really
wish you could see this.

04:35.141 --> 04:36.165
(LAUGHING)

04:36.242 --> 04:39.268
You want to hear the pregnancy rap?
It's even worse.

04:39.345 --> 04:42.109
<i>(SINGING) You get much more
from your pelvic floor</i>

04:42.181 --> 04:44.581
<i>When you pass on the bagel
and do one more Kegel</i>

04:44.651 --> 04:45.675
(GRACE LAUGHING)

04:45.752 --> 04:50.416
Jesus Christ. Tell me, do I have to be
this uncool for the rest of my life?

04:50.990 --> 04:53.390
What are you doing?
You're talking to me 
while you're exercising?

04:53.459 --> 04:54.949
No, I'm just watching it.

04:55.028 --> 04:57.155
I have this subdural
hematoma thing due Friday.

04:57.230 --> 04:59.095
I'm trying to finish it
before we go out tonight.

04:59.165 --> 05:01.531
Out? You two? Where?

05:01.601 --> 05:03.068
Dinner at Burt's parents'.

05:03.136 --> 05:04.262
Ooh!

05:05.438 --> 05:07.406
They must be
out-of-their-minds excited.

05:07.473 --> 05:08.565
Yeah, you know them.

05:08.641 --> 05:11.201
I think they're probably happy to be
the only set of grandparents

05:11.277 --> 05:13.006
and have the baby
to themselves.

05:13.079 --> 05:15.775
Don't say that. You're lucky
to have them so close.

05:15.848 --> 05:18.908
I know, I know.
We're gonna lean pretty hard on them.

05:18.985 --> 05:20.509
You know I'd be there if I could.

05:20.586 --> 05:22.349
I hate that I'll be so far away.

05:22.422 --> 05:23.946
I know.

05:24.023 --> 05:25.581
Who do you think she'll look like?

05:25.658 --> 05:27.523
God, I hope she doesn't have Burt's...

05:27.593 --> 05:28.753
What, facial hair?

05:28.828 --> 05:29.920
Feet.

05:29.996 --> 05:31.793
(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)
Those feet. Square feet.

05:31.864 --> 05:33.525
(LAUGHING)
Like seal flippers.

05:33.599 --> 05:34.827
(GRACE LAUGHING)

05:34.901 --> 05:38.337
Oh! Shit, I just gave
this guy's brain a vulva.

05:39.839 --> 05:43.240
BURT: I really want her to have
an epic kind of childhood.

05:43.309 --> 05:47.939
I want her to run along streams
and know how to work a canoe,

05:48.014 --> 05:49.982
be able to entertain
herself outside.

05:50.049 --> 05:53.576
I want her childhood to be Huck Finn-y.
You know?

05:54.554 --> 05:56.522
Yeah. I had that.

05:59.692 --> 06:01.956
Yeah, exactly.

06:03.196 --> 06:04.993
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

06:10.436 --> 06:12.233
(IN HUSKY VOICE)
Burt Farlander.

06:12.305 --> 06:15.172
Oh! Oh! Oh!

06:15.241 --> 06:17.539
You old so-and-so.

06:18.544 --> 06:21.206
I'm sorry about
your Pacers, my friend.

06:21.280 --> 06:25.649
Hey, if you think Mike Dunleavy can
carry more than a bucket of water,

06:25.718 --> 06:29.745
I got some Florida swampland you
might be interested in. Yeah.

06:29.822 --> 06:30.811
That's loud.

06:30.890 --> 06:31.948
No, real good price.

06:32.024 --> 06:33.355
(LAUGHING)

06:37.463 --> 06:40.193
Yeah. Yeah.

06:40.833 --> 06:44.234
Oh! That one gets me
every time. Yeah.

06:44.303 --> 06:46.897
Well, I'm glad you called. Yeah.

06:48.174 --> 06:49.402
(SIGHS)

07:07.126 --> 07:08.150
(LAUGHING)

07:08.227 --> 07:12.163
You're too much.
All right, I will. Bye.

07:20.706 --> 07:22.799
They expect that from me.

07:23.743 --> 07:26.678
They expect you to sound
like Casey Kasem.

07:27.447 --> 07:30.439
Verona, most of these guys
are in their 50s and 60s.

07:30.516 --> 07:32.950
We're talking about millions of dollars
in insurance futures.

07:33.019 --> 07:37.422
They don't want to be dealing with some
33-year-old that didn't finish college.

07:37.490 --> 07:40.755
So, Casey Kasem finished college?

07:41.627 --> 07:43.151
Yeah.

07:44.897 --> 07:46.159
(SCOFFS)

07:47.867 --> 07:49.732
(IN HUSKY VOICE) This next
long-distance dedication...
No.

07:49.802 --> 07:53.966
goes out to a really special girl.
The letter reads,

07:54.040 --> 07:59.672
"Dear Casey, my name is Burt, and my
girlfriend's pregnant and frustrated.

07:59.745 --> 08:05.274
"Could you play a song that will make her smile?
Thanks. Signed, Burt Farlander."

08:06.352 --> 08:09.446
Your pregnant girlfriend's
gonna kill you.

08:16.395 --> 08:17.828
Go away.

08:17.897 --> 08:18.955
Thanks, Casey.

08:40.253 --> 08:44.417
Oh! Look at you!
You look so big!

08:44.490 --> 08:46.390
Good for you!
Hi.

08:46.459 --> 08:47.926
Wow, look at your hair.

08:47.994 --> 08:49.018
I freed it!

08:49.095 --> 08:50.756
I don't think it makes
you look crazy at all.

08:50.830 --> 08:54.664
I know, I know. Get inside.
Your father's just finishing up a call.

08:54.834 --> 08:57.234
Sit, Verona. Sit next to me and
let me hear the heartbeat.

08:57.303 --> 09:00.431
You can't hear the heartbeat
'cause her placenta is on... Okay.

09:00.506 --> 09:01.530
JERRY: Well, Bill, if you believe that,

09:01.607 --> 09:05.236
I've got a bridge in New York
you might be interested in.
Yep, okay.

09:05.311 --> 09:07.245
That is really sweet.
JERRY: Au revoir.

09:09.882 --> 09:12.874
Hey, Jerry. You're looking so much better.
You can barely tell.

09:12.952 --> 09:15.420
Oh! Thank you, my dear.

09:15.488 --> 09:17.547
Verona, you look beautific.

09:17.623 --> 09:18.647
Thank you.

09:18.724 --> 09:20.316
GLORIA: Hey, did you bring the pictures
from the sonogram?

09:20.393 --> 09:21.883
I did. Here you go, Dad.

09:21.961 --> 09:23.690
These are fabulous.

09:23.763 --> 09:25.094
You haven't opened
the envelope yet.

09:25.164 --> 09:27.064
I can just tell he's a beauty.

09:27.133 --> 09:28.464
She's a girl.
Did you...

09:28.534 --> 09:30.229
Yes. I did tell
you that, Dad.

09:30.303 --> 09:34.672
She's a beauty.
Wow. Spectacular.

09:35.608 --> 09:38.975
Exquisite. I mean,
talk about perfection.

09:39.045 --> 09:41.138
Verona, do you think
she's gonna look like you?

09:41.213 --> 09:43.340
Well, I hope so.
I think I'm the mom.

09:43.416 --> 09:45.043
I just want a little Verona.

09:45.117 --> 09:48.644
After 2 boys, I want a little Verona
in a leotard. Can you do that for me?

09:48.721 --> 09:51.656
I will definitely
work on it.

09:51.724 --> 09:54.090
Okay, and just how black
do you think she'll be?

09:54.160 --> 09:55.525
Mom...

09:55.595 --> 09:58.029
Wow. I don't know.

09:58.097 --> 10:02.056
Maybe we can leave her out in the sun
for a couple of days, expedite things?

10:02.134 --> 10:03.465
Verona, are you on schedule?

10:03.536 --> 10:05.936
Oh! Jerry!
You don't ask her that!

10:06.005 --> 10:08.838
But I'll tell you what scares me,
it's that tilted uterus of yours.

10:08.908 --> 10:09.966
Does it really?

10:10.042 --> 10:12.442
Do you think that's gonna
make the delivery hell?

10:12.511 --> 10:13.500
I don't know.

10:13.579 --> 10:14.944
You know how I had this one?
Yes.

10:15.014 --> 10:16.038
Yeah.
Thank you.

10:16.115 --> 10:17.810
In the tub. Uh-huh.
Yep.

10:17.883 --> 10:20.579
I had to call the fire department,
it happened so fast.

10:20.653 --> 10:22.177
The water broke,
I make the call.

10:22.254 --> 10:25.280
10 minutes later, 3 firemen
burst in the bathroom.

10:25.358 --> 10:26.985
You've got to picture me.
No, we don't.

10:27.059 --> 10:32.588
I'm 23, gorgeous, alone, the skirt's hiked
up to the waist, the legs are apart,

10:32.665 --> 10:34.530
I'm huffing and puffing, and bang!

10:34.600 --> 10:37.364
I'm surrounded by the 3 men
in the uniforms.

10:37.436 --> 10:38.460
(SIGHS)

10:38.537 --> 10:40.767
It's August, so humid.

10:40.840 --> 10:43.502
My blouse is soaked,
I'm engorged with milk...

10:43.576 --> 10:46.272
Did they bring their hoses, Gloria?

10:46.345 --> 10:48.336
They were all over me.

10:49.715 --> 10:53.378
Very capable men, knew exactly
what they were doing.

10:56.355 --> 11:02.123
Almighty food gatherer, father of
the earth, sky, water and ice

11:03.529 --> 11:06.430
and food, we give you thanks.

11:06.499 --> 11:08.194
(GLORIA SPEAKS GIBBERISH)

11:08.467 --> 11:09.900
Thank you.

11:12.538 --> 11:13.800
So, we've been reading
a bunch of books,

11:13.873 --> 11:16.467
trying to decide what kind of birthing
experience we want to have.

11:16.542 --> 11:18.271
That's terrific.

11:18.344 --> 11:22.474
And we think that we want to limit
the amount of people in the room,

11:22.548 --> 11:24.243
or near the room.

11:26.619 --> 11:27.984
Well, you don't have
to worry about that.

11:28.054 --> 11:30.454
Right. No sweat.

11:31.157 --> 11:34.593
And we decided that we don't want
any videotaping. Sorry, Jerry.

11:34.660 --> 11:36.890
JERRY: Right, I won't.
Fabulous.

11:38.631 --> 11:40.326
But we really want
to share this with you.

11:40.399 --> 11:42.458
Your presence is really,
really important to us.

11:42.535 --> 11:44.560
Definitely.
Yeah, yeah.

11:44.670 --> 11:46.865
You're so right.
We so are looking forward to it.

11:46.939 --> 11:48.998
We will definitely be there.

11:49.075 --> 11:52.533
The only reason we won't be there
is if we're living in Belgium.

11:53.713 --> 11:54.839
GLORIA: Okay, we have news.

11:54.914 --> 11:55.938
It's big.

11:56.015 --> 11:57.744
What is it?
We're leaving in June.

11:57.817 --> 11:59.216
We're finally doing it.

11:59.285 --> 12:00.547
You're leaving in June?

12:00.619 --> 12:01.643
GLORIA: Mmm-hmm.

12:01.721 --> 12:03.086
The baby's due in July.

12:03.155 --> 12:06.056
Right. To Antwerp.
City of light.

12:06.125 --> 12:08.685
Well, that's not...
No, you're not.

12:08.761 --> 12:10.422
Yeah, we are.
It's gonna be superb.

12:10.496 --> 12:12.623
No. And don't
say that word.

12:12.698 --> 12:13.687
We thought you'd
be proud of us.

12:13.766 --> 12:15.529
We've been talking
about this for 15 years.

12:15.601 --> 12:17.501
And now we can
finally do it.

12:17.570 --> 12:21.529
You're leaving a month
before the baby's born?

12:22.408 --> 12:27.175
You're moving 3,000 miles
away from your grandchild.

12:28.280 --> 12:30.111
I think it's more than
3,000, isn't it, Jerry?

12:30.182 --> 12:31.945
I think so.

12:32.017 --> 12:33.814
I can't believe this!

12:33.886 --> 12:35.114
There are planes, Burt.

12:35.187 --> 12:38.213
We've been planning this forever, folks.
You know that.

12:38.290 --> 12:40.451
I didn't know that.

12:40.526 --> 12:43.620
Wait, hold on a second.
How long are you gonna live there?

12:43.696 --> 12:44.754
GLORIA: Just 2 years. Okay?

12:44.830 --> 12:47.822
"Just 2 years"? You guys.

12:47.900 --> 12:50.425
Wait. Are you selling the house?

12:50.503 --> 12:53.472
See, that's the best part.
We were going to rent the house out

12:53.539 --> 12:56.474
with the help of a very elegant
gentleman named Fareed,

12:56.542 --> 12:58.009
but no one's come forward yet. So...

12:58.077 --> 13:00.068
Wait. How long have you
been planning this?

13:00.146 --> 13:02.671
Hold on. If we don't find
a renter in the next month,

13:02.748 --> 13:04.443
you two can stay here
while we're gone.

13:04.517 --> 13:06.747
You can have the house
for the next 2 years.

13:06.819 --> 13:07.979
Outstanding.

13:08.053 --> 13:09.577
(PHONE RINGING)

13:16.562 --> 13:18.962
GLORIA: Were
your ears burning?

13:19.031 --> 13:21.591
Your ears must
have been on fire, sir.

13:21.667 --> 13:23.032
What is that?

13:23.102 --> 13:24.126
Oh!

13:24.203 --> 13:28.435
Magnificent, isn't it?
I didn't think you'd notice. $12,000.

13:29.675 --> 13:31.108
I cannot believe it.

13:31.177 --> 13:33.543
I know.
She's a Choctaw princess, I'm told.

13:33.612 --> 13:37.810
I think it's important
that we honor our Indian...

13:37.883 --> 13:40.909
Indigent people...
Our ingenious...

13:42.087 --> 13:44.112
In-de-gentious people.

13:46.826 --> 13:48.555
Who was it?

13:48.627 --> 13:49.616
Nobody.

13:52.231 --> 13:53.789
(CLEARS THROAT)

13:54.266 --> 13:55.528
Was it... Was it Fareed?

13:55.601 --> 13:56.727
Later.

13:56.802 --> 13:58.531
Later.
Hmm.

13:59.672 --> 14:01.640
If it was Fareed,
did he...

14:01.707 --> 14:02.935
Yeah.

14:03.008 --> 14:04.908
He did? He...
Mmm-hmm.

14:06.812 --> 14:08.211
(SCREAMING)

14:11.383 --> 14:13.146
When?
The day we leave.

14:13.219 --> 14:14.880
Oh, my God!

14:15.521 --> 14:18.615
I guess we've got some
more news for you two.

14:20.626 --> 14:22.719
We could get someone else
to be the grandparents.

14:22.795 --> 14:25.457
Those old people, across the street,
what are their names?

14:25.531 --> 14:27.260
I mean, we moved
here for them.

14:27.333 --> 14:30.825
And now, they're gonna miss
the baby's first 2 years.

14:31.503 --> 14:34.995
It just really takes selfishness
to a whole new level.

14:37.743 --> 14:40.837
It's not like your parents
are doing anything.

14:41.180 --> 14:43.705
My parents are dead, Burt.

14:44.283 --> 14:45.750
Still.

14:52.658 --> 14:54.489
I can see my breath.

14:54.560 --> 14:57.120
Hold on, I'll get the thing.

14:57.196 --> 15:00.927
Make it nice and toasty.
There you go.

15:01.000 --> 15:02.467
(ELECTRICITY SURGES)

15:02.534 --> 15:04.263
God damn it.
Great.

15:04.336 --> 15:06.167
All I did
was turn it on.

15:06.238 --> 15:09.696
I even said to the guy at the store,
I said, "Could I have a red fuse?"

15:09.775 --> 15:10.969
He said, "You want a blue fuse."

15:11.043 --> 15:12.340
I said, "No, I already
had the blue fuse.

15:12.411 --> 15:15.847
"Didn't work out great.
So I'll take a red one."

15:15.915 --> 15:19.043
He's like, "Trust me,
it's the blue one." "Okay."

15:19.118 --> 15:22.554
Now we know who will be getting
a red fuse next time.

15:24.223 --> 15:28.353
Burt. You know, we don't have
to stay here.

15:29.929 --> 15:31.123
What?

15:31.830 --> 15:33.764
I'm saying we could leave, too.

15:33.832 --> 15:35.231
But we live here.

15:35.301 --> 15:39.237
I know, but the only reason that we're here
is because your parents are here.

15:39.305 --> 15:41.239
Or were here.

15:43.309 --> 15:44.469
Well, where would we go?

15:44.543 --> 15:46.807
I don't know.
We could go anywhere we want.

15:46.879 --> 15:47.937
Anywhere, anywhere?

15:48.013 --> 15:49.002
Yeah.

15:49.081 --> 15:50.810
I can do my job from anywhere.

15:50.883 --> 15:52.851
And all you need's a phone, right?

15:52.918 --> 15:55.352
Well, we don't want to go
back to Chicago, do we?

15:55.421 --> 15:57.321
No, we did Chicago.

15:58.390 --> 16:02.349
I used to picture myself in Alaska.
God, I love that landscape.

16:02.428 --> 16:03.952
Alaska?
Yeah.

16:04.029 --> 16:06.463
You've never mentioned Alaska.

16:07.366 --> 16:10.767
Wow, they pay people
to live in Alaska.

16:11.036 --> 16:12.060
Oh!

16:12.137 --> 16:16.836
Phoenix. We could
live near my sister.

16:16.909 --> 16:19.901
She could be Auntie Grace
all the time.

